sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0034
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Varies from -6 to +1 region from original sequence to accomodate BioBricks suffix.

No secondary structures are formed in the given RBS region. Users should check for secondary structures induced in the RBS by upstream and downstream elements in the +50 to -50 region, as such structures will greatly affect the strength of the RBS. Contact info for this part: Brian Chow
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Vinay S Mahajan, Voichita D. Marinescu, Brian Chow, Alexander D Wissner-Gross and Peter Carr IAP, 2003.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: rhII
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: autoinducer synthetase for N-butyryl-HSL (BHL) and HHL
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Autoinducer synthesis protein that produces N-butyryl-HSL which binds to RhlR, obtained from Pseudomonas aeruginosa.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Editing Check (1/28/04) (0) BB sites cleaned (1) ATG (2) TAATAA (3) Blast checks out (i.e., it's RhlI) (4) Codon changes OK (AA and tRNA usage) (5) Chassis might have conflict (w/ native autoinducer system?) (6) ssrA tag added (7) barcode added (8) Codon optimized for expression in enteric bacteria

2 silent point mutations have been included into the sequence at base 138 from A to G and at base 576 from G to C to remove internal EcoRI and PstI sites. Mutations were chosen to yield the same amino acid and codons of similar frequency in E. coli.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Debra Lin, Srini Devadas, David Gray, Ronny Krashinsky, and Chris Zheng Liu, Boopers

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0012
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Derived from the TE terminator of T7 bacteriophage between Genes 1.3 and 1.4 <genbank>V01146</genbank>.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Transcription terminator for the E.coli RNA polymerase.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Suggested by Sri Kosuri and Drew Endy as a high efficiency terminator. The 5' end cutoff was placed immediately after the TAA stop codon and the 3' end cutoff was placed just prior to the RBS of Gene 1.4 (before AAGGAG).

Use anywhere transcription should be stopped when the gene of interest is upstream of this terminator.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Reshma Shetty

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: aiiA
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: autoinducer inactivation enzyme from Bacillus; hydrolyzes acetyl homoserine lactone
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance:
AF196486 from Bacillus sp. 240B1 putative metallohydrolase (aiiA) gene.
Dong,Y.H., Xu,J.L., Li,X.Z. and Zhang,L.H.: AiiA, an enzyme that inactivates the acylhomoserine lactone quorum-sensing signal and attenuates the virulence of Erwinia
carotovora, Proc. Natl. Acad. Sci. U.S.A. 97 (7), 3526-3531 (2000).
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Coding region for the autoinducer inactivation enzyme A (aiiA) LVA tagged.
